 clinician referral and specialist advice criteria","locator":"official recommendations lines 134–151","evidence_summary":"Supports documenting clinician-identified serious illness, periorbital location, unusual exposure, treatment non-response, lymphangitis, oral-intake limitation, and an already made referral or specialist discussion; it does not generate urgency."}]}],"evidence_links":[{"evidence_item_id":"derm-skin-infection-follow-up--nice-ng141-cellulitis-reassessment","source_id":"nice-cellulitis-erysipelas-ng141-2019","source_section_id":"nice-ng141-cellulitis-reassessment","direct_relationship":"The exact skin-infection reassessment section supports documenting interval history, change, symptoms, clinician skin inspection, distribution or extent, general appearance, secondary infection signs, severe pain, immune context and already available microbiology without asserting cellulitis, erysipelas, or treatment failure.","paraphrased_evidence_summary":"Supports documenting rapid or significant worsening, lack of improvement, systemic illness, pain out of proportion, spread, underlying conditions, serious alternative diagnoses, and microbiology results during clinician reassessment.","content_mapping_status":"reviewed_not_mapped_to_legacy_content","candidate_status":"review_only_not_approved","source_resolves":true},{"evidence_item_id":"derm-skin-infection-follow-up--nice-ng141-cellulitis-referral","source_id":"nice-cellulitis-erysipelas-ng141-2019","source_section_id":"nice-ng141-cellulitis-referral","direct_relationship":"The exact clinician-referral section supports documenting a clinician-entered plan, safety net, arranged follow-up and patient questions only; it does not generate escalation.","paraphrased_evidence_summary":"Supports documenting clinician-identified serious illness, periorbital location, unusual exposure, treatment non-response, lymphangitis, oral-intake limitation, and an already made referral or specialist discussion; it does not generate